When Exporting a customized columns filter using _Excel (Current Fields)_, the exported Excel file revert the columns to the default configuration.
h3. Steps to produce:
 # Create a filter in advanced mode using JQL, for example the following JQL:
{code:java}
project = "Demonstration Project" AND resolution is EMPTY
{code}

 # Save the filter
 # Change the filter column order to show a field such as _Labels_ field
 # Export the filter to _Excel_, the filter will be correctly exported.
 # Now,add another JQL clause to the previous JQL query for instance:
{code:java}
AND labels = abc
{code}

 # Export the filter to _Excel_ (without saving the changes to the filter). You will notice the columns will revert to the My Defaults configuration (without the Labels column)

h3. Workaround:

Save the modified filter before exporting to _Excel_
 Detailed at: [https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/Column+order+when+exporting+a+filter+search]

